Certainly! Here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "imaj" in different forms and positions, with a star (*) indicating the word:

1. *Imaj* na umu da je sutra praznik. (Keep in mind that tomorrow is a holiday.)
2. Kada *imaš* vremena, dođi da te upoznam s mojim prijateljima. (When you have time, come and meet my friends.)
3. On *ima* puno novca, ali to nije sve u životu. (He has a lot of money, but that's not everything in life.)
4. Da li *ima* neko ideju kako da rešimo ovaj problem? (Does anyone have an idea how to solve this problem?)
5. Ne *imaj* strah, nećemo ti ništa loše uraditi. (Don't be afraid, we won't do anything bad to you.)
6. *Imajmo* malo strpljenja, sve će se rešiti. (Let's have a little patience, everything will be resolved.)
7. Ako *imaš* bilo kakvih pitanja, slobodno me pitaj. (If you have any questions, feel free to ask me.)
8. *Imajući* u vidu tvoje uslove, mislim da ova ponuda ne bi bila prihvatljiva za tebe. (Considering your conditions, I don't think this offer would be acceptable for you.)
9. Nisam siguran da *imam* dovoljno novca da kupim novi automobil. (I'm not sure if I have enough money to buy a new car.)
10. *Imao* sam veoma lep odmor prošlog leta. (I had a very nice vacation last summer.)